Trewia nudiflora

    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Euphorbiales:Euphorbiaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 10489

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   Medium sized to tall deciduous tree often with a short bole, but on
   good sites with a long straight bole, often much buttressed at the
   base.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   Pitali, Iumri, Khamara, Bhillaur, Gumhar, Kat kumbla, Pitari, Yehmyok,
   Setkadon.
   FURTHER INF
   Pitali can be found in India, Bangladesh and Myanmar, particularly
   along rivers and streams and on moist and swampy sites. In youth the
   tree can withstand light shade. It is sensitive to drought. Yearly
   volume production potential is about 15-30 m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Zabala N 1990 pp 93-95 [TEMP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT, USE]
   Troup R 1921 pp 841-844 [USE, DRA, FER, LIG, KTMP]

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
